NAME
	comp-list (tk-display) - list the compositions in a directory as Tk buttons that load the chosen one via the Matrix ctl file

INTERFACE
	tk-display (MatrixTkDisplay)

READS
	<mount>		a directory of composition files (normally
			/lib/matrix/compositions).

WRITES
	/mnt/matrix/ctl	"load <name>" when a button is pressed.

DESCRIPTION
	The module behind the default picker composition
	(/lib/matrix/compositions/picker).  It enumerates the mount
	directory, skips the picker composition itself, and builds one
	full-width Tk button per composition; a press writes
	"load <name>" to the Matrix control file, replacing the current
	composition in place.  The buttons are real Tk widgets on
	purpose: the engine owns their geometry and routing, so the
	click target IS the tile — and, like every Tk widget, they are
	drivable from Inferno sh.  The directory is rescanned once a
	second (MatrixTicker); the button column rebuilds only when the
	set of compositions changes.

	Because the picker is itself an ordinary crystallisation wired
	to this module, users and agents can edit or replace it like
	any other composition.

SEE ALSO
	/lib/matrix/compositions/picker (the crystallisation using this)
	docs/matrix-architecture.md (the ctl load verb)
